node.text: So dark up top in the woods 😳The weather has finally cleared up a little and was able to do some training at the local on my DH bike for the first time in ages! 🙏🏻🙏🏻🙏🏻 extremely fortunate to be allowed to carry on training during this time.

node.text: Follow Kade Edwards and Kaos Seagrave down the “Full Moto” line at Black Mountain Cycles Centre, UK, aboard Tahnée Seagrave’s #GOPRO #HERO7 head cam. #dh #mtb #pov #dhmtb #headcam #redbull

node.text:
Tomorrow we go hunting!!! ⚔️😤🌈
This track is truly challenging in every way, but I’m enjoying piecing the puzzle together… 🧩 📸 @maddogboris 

My run is at 12:28 UK time, you can watch it on RedBull TV and also BBC!

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Tahnée Seagrave in VAL DI SOLE. May be a closeup of 1 person and outdoors.

node.text:
A tough decision today but confident it’s the right one! I’ve been struggling with my neck ever since the slipped disk and this track is SO demanding physically and mentally. I had a great day in practice yesterday, but it was a little much for my neck and I woke up super stiff, aware that riding my bike makes it worse… I decided to sit out today. Luckily with my protected status I am able to just break the beam in Qualies which means I will still be able to race on Sunday. Trying to give myself the best chance at doing the best job possible on race day. Let’s get it. 👊🏻
📸 @svenmartinphoto

node.text:
The Dark Horse 🖤🤍 New World Champs set up is sick! 

Also running the brand new @foxmtb #RPC lid. Similar shape to the old one, but lighter and comfier. Now available!

Not the usual custom paint job, but @canyon are running an incredible campaign with @worldbicyclerelief. By donating you can win a bike! Check their posts for more. X

Photos are @davetrumporephoto

node.text:
Maribor World Cup iPhone photo dump! The things you don’t always see 😆

1. Race run warm up, trying to cool down after warming up in the already extremely hot weather? 🤨
2. Proof of said extremely hot weather 🥵
3. Getting a pic of my swollen hand to show @point1athletic 
4. Keeping cool 
5.  I was reluctant about this but took it because you guys never see this side… things don’t ever really go to plan and I doubt myself enormously, like most people do!
6. The track was F#CKD 😂
7. Cuts n bruises
8. More cuts n bruises
9. Broken Van
10. Silver linings of a broken down van 🥰🥰🥰

node.text:
Always learning! This sport never fails to teach me something new 💕 Although in a good head space this week, my body wasn’t quite up to scratch after the wreck! Another 5th place. Very happy with my performance and leaving me hungry for more!!! The progress of the women’s field recently is insane and something I’m so proud to be apart of. 💪🏻 Big love x
Photos @maddogboris

Friday 13th bit HARD! Big slam in training. Otherwise feeling good, tough track to know where the limit is. Guess I found it 🤷🏼‍♀️😂😭 Let’s hope the body is feeling ok for Qualifying tomorrow. 💪🏻❣️
📸 @maddogboris

OMG! Took a few weeks off the big bike and we are BACK! Never have I ever seen home in dry conditions and boooyyyy did the new stuff at @revolutionbp deliver today!!!!! 🥵💥 Thanks for the good vibes @parfitt34 @veroniquesandler ❣️

Ffar side was my favourite track ever and I was so sad when it got destroyed. Sad no longer!!!! Even more so my favourite track now 😁 get yourselves there ASAP!!!!!
